&lt;h2&gt;
	printing in ABS&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	I used ABS for this instead of PLA because it is supposedly better for mechanical parts. What surprised me was how much it shrunk. The whole thing shrunk almost 2mm (~3%), which made it a little loose on the tripod. If you are designing something for ABS, remember to calibrate your skeinforge settings or scale your stl file before you print.&lt;/p&gt;
